cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with deep learning-based approaches for universal lesion detection on CT images, which is a problem related to computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes to incorporate domain knowledge in clinical practice into the model design, which is related to artificial intelligence (AI). The paper also mentions the use of attention modules, which are commonly used in multimedia (MM) and information retrieval (IR) tasks.
